abstract = {Remote Sensing (RS) is a vital technology used in several applications that enable remote measurements for sensors in a certain Area of Interest (AoI), which in turn will assist decision-making in taking the right decision. This technology, like many others, has witnessed a tremendous improvement due to the development of new technologies such as Machine learning, cloud computing, the internet of things (IoT). In addition, many supportive wireless communication protocols have been evolved such as Long Range Wide Area Networks (LoRaWAN), Zigbee, Narrow Band IoT (NB-IoT), Long Term Evolution for Machines (LTE-M), SigFox, and others. This book chapter aims to discuss several network architecture and techniques that can be used to provide smart yet efficient remote sensing functionality that can be used for many safety-critical applications, namely nature disaster detection that has particular importance for authorities and decision-makers due to its disastrous effect both economically and socially.}
