abstract = {Effective management of Earth's resources is critical for sustainable development and environmental stewardship. Integrating artificial intelligence (AI) presents a promising avenue for optimizing resource management practices and achieving long-term sustainability. This abstract explores the potential of AI-powered intelligent solutions in Earth resource management for sustainable stewardship. AI offers advanced data processing, pattern recognition, and predictive modeling capabilities. AI algorithms can extract valuable insights and patterns by analyzing large volumes of data from diverse sources such as satellite imagery, sensors, and socio-economic indicators. These insights enable informed decision-making, strategic planning, and sustainable practice implementation. Intelligent solutions powered by AI in Earth resource management encompass various domains. AI can optimize agriculture irrigation schedules, crop monitoring, and disease detection, improving productivity and efficient water usage. For energy management, AI can optimize power distribution, integrate renewable energy sources, and forecast energy demand, enabling the transition to clean and sustainable energy systems. Furthermore, AI plays a crucial role in environmental monitoring and conservation. Through satellite imagery and environmental data analysis, AI can detect ecosystem changes, identify vulnerable areas, and support conservation efforts. It aids in biodiversity monitoring, early warning systems for natural disasters, and preventing illegal activities that harm the environment. Data availability, interoperability, and ethical considerations must be addressed to fully leverage intelligent solutions for Earth resource management. Ensuring data privacy, transparency, and fairness in AI algorithms is crucial for building trust and promoting responsible use. Innovative solutions empowered by AI have the potential to revolutionize Earth's resource management and facilitate sustainable